{meta: title The Kentuckian Song}
{meta: artist Anita Carter}
{meta: composer Irving Gordon}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I see my darling in [F]each spray of summer [C]sunlight
[D7]I see my darling in the leaves that [G7]fall
[C]I see him walking in the rainy [F]April [C]showers
[G7]And hear his name in every bluebird [C]call
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]I told the possum in the gumtree the raccoon on the [C]ground
[F]Told everyone bout [C]my darling of the [D7]happiness I [G7]found
[C]My heart would cry more than the [F]weeping willow [C]tree
[G7]If my darling and his heart were not for [C]me
{end_of_verse}

